rComments: She's really nice and really smart, I enjoyed being in her class. She's also very approachable and helpful. If you end up taking her class I encourage you to go to her office hours because she will help guide you to the right direction.

Personally, I could use a little less focus on poetry, but she breaks up the syllabus with light weeks of reading to allow you time to get through the novels. A non-conventional reading of the text will impress her on essays, as long as you back it up with evidence. She's really great.
Thoroughly covered texts and organized lectures. She made expectations extremely clear concerning marks which helped alot.
Her lectures are very structured and clear.  She made the subject material interesting, and was very thorough. Though she is a hard marker, she is clear in her expectations.  I enjoyed her class.
